(Match 118)  26th February 1921  (British Championship)
NORTHERN IRELAND - SCOTLAND  0-2  (0-1)
Referee:   Arthur Ward (England)
Crowd:     40.000, Windsor Park, Belfast
Goals:     0-1 Wilson (10) penalty, 0-2 Cassidy (87)
NORTHERN IRELAND:
Elisha Scott - James Mulligan, David Rollo - William Lacey, Ernest Edwin Smith, Michael Terence 
O'Brien - Samuel McGregor, James Ferris, Daniel McKinney, Michael Hamill, Louis James Arthur Oscar
Buckhalter "Bookman".

SCOTLAND:
Kenneth Campbell                     (5/Partick Thistle) -
John Marshall                                                 (2/Middlesbrough)
William McStay                                                               (2/Celtic) -
Joseph Harris                                                                                        (2/Partick Thistle)
John Alexander Graham                                                                                                (1/Arsenal)
James McMullan                                                                                                               (3/Partick Thistle) -
Alexander McNab                                                                                                                                       (1/Greenock Morton)
Thomas Miller                                                                                                                                                           (2/Manchester United)
Andrew Nesbit Wilson [c]             (5/Dunfermline Athletic)
Joseph Cassidy                                           (2/Celtic)
Alexander Troup                                                              (3/Dundee)

Notes:  Louis James Arthur Oscar Buckhalter (or Buchalter), was a Lithuanian Jewish footballer and 
        cricketer who represented his adopted country, Ireland, at both sports. The Buckhalter family 
        emigrated from Lithuania to Ireland in the 1890s to escape anti-Semitism and subsequently 
        changed their name to Bookman.  
                      


